# Projects Section

## Overview
Full viewport section with section label, heading, and a
horizontal scrollable row of 6 project cards.
Each card has an SVG architecture diagram, title, description,
SCOPE/TECH toggle tabs, and a View Case Study CTA.

## Section id
id="projects"

## Layout
- Full viewport: min-h-screen
- Section padding: same as About — px-6 md:px-16 lg:px-24
- Top border: border-t border-[var(--custom-border)]
- Background: var(--bg-primary)
- Section label: "02 — PROJECTS"
- Heading: "Featured Work"

## Horizontal Scroll Container
- overflow-x: auto, overflow-y: hidden
- scroll-behavior: smooth
- Hide scrollbar (custom CSS)
- display: flex, gap: 1.5rem
- padding-bottom: 1.5rem (for scrollbar space)
- Cursor: grab while dragging
- Mouse drag to scroll — implement with mousedown/mousemove/mouseup
- Touch scroll native

## Card Specs
- Width: 360px — fixed, flex-shrink: 0
- Min-height: 560px
- Background: var(--bg-card)
- Border: 1px solid var(--custom-border)
- Border radius: 16px
- Padding: 0 (image flush to top, content padded inside)
- Hover: border-color → var(--lime), translateY(-6px)
- Transition: all 300ms ease

## Card Structure (top to bottom)
1. Diagram container — top of card, no padding, overflow hidden, rounded-t-2xl
   - Height: 180px
   - Contains SVG diagram component
   - On hover: diagram scales to 1.04 (zoom effect)
   - Background: var(--bg-secondary)

2. Content area — padding: 1.5rem
   - Project number: font-display, text-xs, muted, mb-1
   - Title: font-display, text-lg, bold, text-primary, mb-2
   - Description: font-body, text-sm, text-secondary, leading-relaxed, mb-4
   - SCOPE/TECH toggle: two buttons side by side
   - Tab content: min-height 80px, text-sm
   - Tech badges: flex-wrap, gap-1.5, mt-3
   - Divider: 1px border-t border-[var(--custom-border)], my-4
   - CTA: "View Case Study →" text link, lime color, hover arrow animates right

## SCOPE/TECH Toggle
- Two pill buttons: SCOPE | TECH
- Active: bg-[var(--lime)] text-black
- Inactive: border border-[var(--custom-border)] text-muted
- State managed per card with useState
- Default active tab: SCOPE

## SCOPE Tab Content
- Shows project metric (large, lime colored)
- Shows scope description text (small, muted)

## TECH Tab Content
- Shows tech stack badges
- Badge style: text-xs, border border-[var(--custom-border)],
  rounded-full, px-2 py-0.5, text-secondary

## SVG Diagrams
Each project has a unique SVG diagram component.
Located in: components/diagrams/
- SocWorkflowDiagram.tsx
- ContactCentreXdrDiagram.tsx
- Fido2AuthDiagram.tsx
- MdrPlatformDiagram.tsx
- EndpointSecurityDiagram.tsx
- EaPlayDiagram.tsx

SVG style rules:
- ViewBox: "0 0 360 180"
- Background: transparent (card bg shows through)
- Node boxes: fill var(--bg-card), stroke var(--custom-border)
- Arrow lines: stroke var(--lime), strokeWidth 1.5
- Text labels: fill var(--text-muted), font-size 10px
- Key/primary nodes: stroke var(--lime)
- Font: var(--font-display)

## Drag to Scroll
Implement with useRef on scroll container:
- onMouseDown: set isDragging true, record startX
- onMouseMove: if isDragging, scroll container by delta
- onMouseUp/onMouseLeave: set isDragging false
- cursor: grab normally, grabbing while dragging

## Dot Indicators
- Row of dots below scroll container
- One dot per card
- Active dot: lime color, wider (12px)
- Inactive: var(--custom-border), 8px
- Update active dot based on scroll position

## Animations
- Section heading: fade up on scroll into view
- Cards: stagger fade up as section enters viewport
  delay: index * 0.1

## Rules
- "use client" required
- CSS Modules: Projects.module.css
- All text from useTranslation('projects')
- Add 'projects' to Namespace in lib/i18n/config.ts
- No inline styles
- No hardcoded colors